<subSubSection id="27B181EDFFEE1E2FFEC4FD272597FB93" pageId="3" pageNumber="46" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="6F14D266FFEE1E2FFEC4FD272597FB93" blockId="3.[280,1778,613,1585]" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">
The identity of 
<taxonomicName id="A8ABA9E5FFEE1E2FFDD5FD2726F8FCA6" authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1858" box="[594,724,735,772]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Laphria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bella">
<emphasis id="5DDF0E74FFEE1E2FFDD5FD272642FCA6" box="[594,622,735,772]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="5DDF0E74FFEE1E2FFD04FD2726F8FCA6" box="[643,724,735,772]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">bella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has never been in doubt. Oldroyd (1974) incorrectly labelled a series of 
<taxonomicName id="A8ABA9E5FFEE1E2FFE5CFCE926E2FC94" box="[475,718,785,822]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Laphria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aureopilosa">
<emphasis id="5DDF0E74FFEE1E2FFE5CFCE925DBFC94" box="[475,503,785,822]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="5DDF0E74FFEE1E2FFD89FCE926E2FC94" box="[526,718,785,822]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">aureopilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
males from Rhodesia as 
<taxonomicName id="A8ABA9E5FFEE1E2FFB14FCE9213FFC94" authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1858" box="[1171,1299,785,822]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Laphria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bella">
<emphasis id="5DDF0E74FFEE1E2FFB14FCE9213FFC94" box="[1171,1299,785,822]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">L. bella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see under 
<taxonomicName id="A8ABA9E5FFEE1E2FFA65FCE922F0FC94" box="[1506,1756,785,822]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Laphria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aureopilosa">
<emphasis id="5DDF0E74FFEE1E2FFA65FCE9222CFC94" box="[1506,1536,785,822]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="5DDF0E74FFEE1E2FF991FCE922C1FC94" box="[1558,1773,785,822]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">aureopilosa).</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
The male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="F790CEE3FFEE1E2FFD34FCBB270DFCCA" box="[691,801,835,872]" captionStart="Figs 1-5" captionStartId="2.[210,272,2476,2508]" captionTargetBox="[255,1619,337,2380]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-5. Choerades species; dorsal aspect of cr genital bulb 1. C. aureopilosa (Ricardo). 2. C. bella (Loew). 3. C. jlavipes (Weidemann). 4. C. nigrescens (Ricardo) 5. C. serpentina (Bezzi)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1472447/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) have not been properly described. Gonopodal setae small, inwardly directed and appear to be fused for only half their length. Distal margin of gonopod extended forming two processes; one being close to the gonopodal setae the other situated more laterally (
<figureCitation id="F790CEE3FFEE1E2FFC4BFC22201BFC5D" box="[972,1079,986,1023]" captionStart="Figs 1-5" captionStartId="2.[210,272,2476,2508]" captionTargetBox="[255,1619,337,2380]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-5. Choerades species; dorsal aspect of cr genital bulb 1. C. aureopilosa (Ricardo). 2. C. bella (Loew). 3. C. jlavipes (Weidemann). 4. C. nigrescens (Ricardo) 5. C. serpentina (Bezzi)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1472447/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Hypandrium long and narrow viewed ventrally.
</paragraph>
